{{Infobox person | name = Bisi Komolafe | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name =Bisi Komolafe Veronica | birth_date =1986 | birth_place =[[Ibadan]], [[Oyo State]] | death_date =31 December 2012 | death_place =University College Hospital, Ibadan | nationality =[[Nigerian]] | other_names = | occupation ={{flat list | * [[actress]] * [[film director]] * [[film producer]]}} | years_active =2008–2012 | known_for = | notable_works = }}
'''Bisi Komolafe''' (1986–2012) was a [[Nigerian]] [[actress]], [[film director]] and [[film producer|producer]] best known for her role in the movies ''Igboro Ti Daru'' and ''[[Aramotu]]''.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2013/01/nollywood-actress-bisi-komolafe-for-burial-in-ibadan-tomorrow/ | title=Nollywood actress, Bisi Komolafe, for burial in Ibadan, tomorrow | work=[[Vanguard (Nigeria)|Vanguard]] | date=3 January 2013 | accessdate=25 August 2015}}</ref>
==Early life and education== Bisi was born in 1986 into a family of five in [[Ibadan]], [[Oyo State]] South-Western [[Nigeria]] where she completed her primary and secondary school education.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.mjemagazine.com/untold-story-of-bisi-komolafes-mysterious-death-she-died-of-spiritual-attack/ | title=Untold Story Of Bisi Komolafe’s Mysterious Death – She Died Of Spiritual Attack | publisher=MJE Magazine | date=4 January 2013 | accessdate=25 August 2015}}</ref> She proceeded to [[Lagos State University]] where she graduated with a degree in [[Business Administration]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.nigeriafilms.com/news/20033/24/pictures-the-untold-story-about-the-mysterious-dea.html | title=PICTURES: THE UNTOLD STORY ABOUT THE MYSTERIOUS DEATH OF MOVIE STAR BISI KOMOLAFE | publisher=Nigeria Films | author=Akinnagbe Akintomide | date=3 January 2013 | accessdate=25 August 2015 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160310234655/http://www.nigeriafilms.com/news/20033/24/pictures-the-untold-story-about-the-mysterious-dea.html | archivedate=10 March 2016 | df= }}</ref>
==Career== Bisi's acting career shot into limelight after she starred in the movie ''Igboro Ti Daru''. She went on to play leading roles in films including ''Bolode O'ku'', ''Asiri Owo'' and ''Ebute''. Bisi also produced movies including ''Latonwa'', ''Eja Tutu'' and ''Oka''.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.pmnewsnigeria.com/2013/01/01/bisi-komolafe-nollywood-actress-dies/ | title=Bisi Komolafe, Nollywood actress dies | work=[[P.M. News]] | author=Bayo Adetutu | date=1 January 2013 | accessdate=25 August 2015}}</ref> She was nominated in the "Revelation of The Year" category at the [[2009 Best of Nollywood Awards]] and in the "Best Lead Actress in a Yoruba film" category at the [[2012 Best of Nollywood Awards|2012 edition]].<ref name="bisi"/>
==Awards and nominations== {| class="wikitable sortable" |- ! Year !! Award ceremony !! Award description !! Result |- | 2009 || [[2009 Best of Nollywood Awards]] || Revelation of The Year || {{nom}}<ref name="bisi">{{cite web | url=http://www.bellanaija.com/2009/12/07/best-of-nollywood-awards-first-photos/ | title=Best of Nollywood Awards 2009 | publisher=[[BellaNaija]] | date=7 December 2009 | accessdate=25 August 2015}}</ref> |- | 2012 || [[2012 Best of Nollywood Awards]] || Best Lead Actress in a Yoruba film || {{nom}}<ref>{{cite web |url = http://nollywoodmindspace.com/2012/09/09/best-of-nollywood-awards-list-of-nominees/ |title = BON Winners |publisher = Nollywood Mindspace |date = 9 September 2012 |accessdate = 25 August 2015 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20141015035529/http://nollywoodmindspace.com/2012/09/09/best-of-nollywood-awards-list-of-nominees/ |archive-date = 2014-10-15 |dead-url = yes |df = }}</ref> |}
==Death== The death of Bisi Komolafe was reported in the media on 31 December 2012.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.nationalmirroronline.net/new/january-2013-highlights-bisi-komolafe-dies/ | title=January 2013 HIGHLIGHTS: Bisi Komolafe dies | work=[[National Mirror]] | author=Oseyiza Ogbodo | date=28 December 2013 | accessdate=25 August 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140824094034/http://nationalmirroronline.net/new/january-2013-highlights-bisi-komolafe-dies/ | archive-date=2014-08-24 | dead-url=yes | df= }}</ref> The circumstances surrounding her death generated several reports and speculations in the media. However medical reports confirmed that she died of pregnancy related complications<ref>{{cite news|url=http://africanspotlight.com/2013/01/07/bisi-komolafes-doctor-speaks-about-her-cause-of-death/|title=Bisi Komolafe's Doctor speaks about her cause of death|publisher=Africa Spotlight|date=January 13, 2013|accessdate=26 August 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170104163630/http://africanspotlight.com/2013/01/07/bisi-komolafes-doctor-speaks-about-her-cause-of-death/|archive-date=2017-01-04|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2013/01/bisi-komolafes-property-tears-fiance-family-apart/ | title=Bisi Komolafe’s property tears fiancé, family apart | work=[[Vanguard (Nigeria)|Vanguard]] | author=Ebun Sessou | date=12 January 2013 | accessdate=25 August 2015}}</ref> at the University College Hospital, Ibadan. She was buried on January 4, 2013<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2013/01/tears-as-bisi-komolafe-goes-home/ | title=Tears as Bisi Komolafe goes home | work=[[Vanguard (Nigeria)|Vanguard]] | author=Ola Ajayi | date=4 January 2013 | accessdate=25 August 2015}}</ref> in Ibadan.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.punchng.com/news/nollywood-actress-bisi-komolafe-buried-amid/|title=Nollywood actress, Bisi Komolafe, buried amid tears|date=January 5, 2013|author=Akinwale Aboluwade|publisher=The Punch|accessdate=25 August 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924130824/http://www.punchng.com/news/nollywood-actress-bisi-komolafe-buried-amid/|archivedate=24 September 2015|df=}}</ref>
